The paper utilizes digitalized books and articles to examine the scientific fame of physicists, which involves data analysis and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these sub-categories, cs.DL and cs.DS are the most likely ones as they are directly related to data analysis and management, while cs.IR, cs.SI, and cs.CL are also relevant as they involve information retrieval, social networks, and natural language processing, respectively.
